Place a flat baking tray in the oven and preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Pour the double cream into a saucepan over a high heat. Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat immediately and leave to cool for one minute.Place the egg whites into a bowl and whisk until stiff peaks form.Place the egg yolks and grated cheese in a separate bowl. Whisk together and season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Pour the warm cream over the egg yolks and cheese and mix together well.Spoon a little of the stiff egg whites into the yolk mixture and mix well.Add the rest of the egg white and gently fold together with a metal spoon, being careful to maintain volume.Spoon the soufflé mixture into the pepper half, place onto the hot baking tray and place into the oven to bake for 8 minutes, until the soufflé has risen and is golden.To serve, place the pepper into the centre of a small warm plate.